<title>SWITZERLAND: SOCCER-UEFA REWARDS THREE COUNTRIES FOR FAIR PLAY.</title>
<headline>SOCCER-UEFA REWARDS THREE COUNTRIES FOR FAIR PLAY.</headline>
<dateline>GENEVA 1996-08-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>Norway, England and Sweden were rewarded for their fair play on Thursday with an additional place in the 1997-98 UEFA Cup competition.</p>
<p>Norway headed the UEFA Fair Play rankings for 1995-96 with 8.62 points, ahead of England with 8.61 and Sweden 8.57.</p>
<p>The rankings are based on a formula that takes into account many factors including red and yellow cards, and coaching and spectators' behaviour at matches played at an international level by clubs and national teams.</p>
<p>Only the top three countries are allocated additional places.</p>
<p>The UEFA Fair Play rankings are:  1. Norway			 8.62 points</p>
